config NXP_IGF
	bool "NXP IGF (Input Glitch Filter) driver"
	default y
	depends on DT_HAS_NXP_IMX_IGF_ENABLED
	help
	  Enable the NXP Input Glitch Filter (IGF) driver. The IGF filters
	  glitches out of input signals on i.MX SoCs (e.g. MIMX94398). Channels
	  are configured statically from devicetree child nodes and applied at
	  init time; the driver wraps the fsl_igf HAL and exposes only status
	  read/clear helpers at runtime.
